
@startuml
' Class Diagram for the Transportation Management System

class Location {
  - address: String
}

class Driver {
  - firstName: String
  - lastName: String
  + driveVehicle(vehicle: Vehicle)
}

class Vehicle {
  - vehicleNumber: String
  + assignDriver(driver: Driver)
}

class Truck extends Vehicle {
  - weight: Double
}

class Car extends Vehicle {
  - seats: Integer
}

class Van extends Vehicle {
  - capacity: Integer
}

class Order {
  - origin: Location
  - destination: Location
  - date: Date
  - driver: Driver
  + assignDriver(driver: Driver)
}

' Associations

Location "1" *-- "0..*" Driver : has
Driver "1" *-- "0..1" Vehicle : drives
Vehicle "1" *-- "0..1" Driver : drivenBy
Driver "1" *-- "0..1" Order : carries
Order "1" -- "1" Location : origin
Order "1" -- "1" Location : destination
@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **`Location`** has an address and can have multiple drivers.
- **`Driver`** has a first and last name, can drive one vehicle at a time, and can carry out one order at a time.
- **`Vehicle`** is an abstract class with a `vehicleNumber`, and can be assigned to one driver.
- **`Truck`**, **`Car`**, and **`Van`** are subclasses of `Vehicle` with specific attributes:
  - `Truck` has a `weight`
  - `Car` has `seats`
  - `Van` has `capacity`
- **`Order`** has an origin and destination location, a date, and one assigned driver.

